channel.title: SFoL 48 - Unseen Chat
channel.description:
Marcus_Doodalee is...
># [color = purple]The Mastermind [/color] >**[color = purple] Unseen Special [/color]** **Can’t Touch This (Passive)** - Immune to death at night, occupation and target changing. Players who attempt to occupy you or change your target will believe it succeeded. Additionally, you will know who you would’ve been redirected to if a player attempts to change your target. **Lurking Presence (Passive)** - If you die, then the starting Assassin will take your place. You appear as Hand of Byzantium to faction checks. **Shadowy Presence (Day)** - Selects what class type you will be shown as to investigators and whether you have Royal Blood or not. Can be used alongside Foresight. - Infinite uses **Foresight (Day)** - Determine a player’s converted class by the end of the day if they can be converted. - 4 uses **Convert (Night)** - Change target player into the Unseen version of their class. If you have failed to convert a target twice already and your next conversion would fail it will instead target a random convertible player. - Infinite uses, 1 night cooldown **Dirty Work (Night)** - If there are no more Unseen members left, you can become The Assassin and you will use Assassinate on your target. - 1 use *Defeat the Hand of Byzantium and any neutrals that seek to do you harm.*

item.title: SFoL 48 - Unseen Chat
item.dc:creator: Marcus_Doodalee
item.description:
@Alice I’d like to change my night action.

/kill Fireslol

Here’s the thing fellas, I expect Datbirb to never occ me realising he is scum
I also expect Baz to protect fireslol from being converted. This is simply because it’s better to stop scum gaining members than for town to lose members usually.
I expect Baz to sometimes go ‘fuck it, I’m just going to guard myself” but with what I’ve said, I don’t think he ever yolo guards fireslol. I think he usually makes fires convert immune, but never death immune.

There is actually a way we can lose the game in every scenario, in fact if I ever get lynched with a convert still around, Blue can sometimes resolve the game into a neutral only win. This forces scum to race or outright win the game, the other scenario has the potential for scum to turn on each other.

In every situation, there is a night action Baz can do to stop scum from auto-winning. I believe this action has the greatest chance of that NOT happening
